    <note>Liu(2) Q [17570] Known as Fengcheng fujun, he was a scholar (boxue), who had a good literary style and his collected papers were transmitted to his descendants. These descendants were not illustrious until his 7th generation descendant, Shixian [17573] (q.v.), who accumulated great wealth--therefore, designation as a family with wealth as status background. The history of this lineage provides a good example of mobility processes. See documentation for descendant, Tingzhi [17575].</note>
